	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A 47-year-old man was arrested for allegedly killing his father with a hammer at Sisonke township in Centane, Eastern Cape police said. In a statement issued on Saturday, police spokesperson Captain Jackson Manatha said the man assaulted his father on Thursday evening after he asked him about his mother's whereabouts. "When the father could not answer the questions from his son, the suspect took his hammer and severely assaulted his father," Manatha said. The father was rushed to hospital and died on Saturday. The suspect is expected to appear in the Centane Magistrate Court on Monday facing a murder charge.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  